The paper deals with video-based face recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves learning a discriminant metric, which is a common task in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of kernel embedding, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
